.TH BW 1 "March 2026" "bitwarden-cli 2026.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bw \- command-line interface for Bitwarden password manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bw
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bw
is the official Bitwarden CLI for managing your vault from the command line
or scripts. It provides full access to all Bitwarden features including
passwords, secure notes, cards, and identities.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B login
Log in to a Bitwarden user account.
.TP
.B logout
Log out of the current user account.
.TP
.B lock
Lock the vault and destroy active session keys.
.TP
.B unlock
Unlock the vault and return a new session key.
.TP
.B sync
Pull the latest vault data from the server.
.TP
.B generate
Generate a password or passphrase.
.TP
.B list
List objects from the vault (items, folders, collections, organizations).
.TP
.B get
Get an object from the vault.
.TP
.B create
Create an object in the vault.
.TP
.B edit
Edit an object in the vault.
.TP
.B delete
Delete an object from the vault.
.TP
.B restore
Restore a deleted object from the trash.
.TP
.B move
Move an item to a folder.
.TP
.B confirm
Confirm an organization member.
.TP
.B import
Import vault data from a file.
.TP
.B export
Export vault data to a file.
.TP
.B share
Move an item to an organization (deprecated, use \fBmove\fR).
.TP
.B send
Manage Bitwarden Send.
.TP
.B receive
Access a Bitwarden Send from a URL.
.TP
.B config
Configure CLI settings.
.TP
.B update
Check for updates.
.TP
.B completion
Generate shell completion scripts.
.TP
.B status
Show the current authentication status.
.TP
.B serve
Start a local API server.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display help information.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information.
.TP
.B \-\-session \fIKEY\fR
Pass session key instead of reading from environment.
.TP
.B \-\-response
Return a JSON formatted version of response output.
.TP
.B \-\-cleanexit
Exit with a return code of 0 unless an error is thrown.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress output to stdout.
.TP
.B \-\-nointeraction
Do not prompt for interactive user input.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BW_SESSION
The session key obtained from \fBbw unlock\fR.
.TP
.B BW_CLIENTID
API client ID for API key authentication.
.TP
.B BW_CLIENTSECRET
API client secret for API key authentication.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/Bitwarden CLI/data.json
Local vault and configuration data.
.SH SEE ALSO
.B bitwarden-desktop\fR(1)
.PP
Full documentation: https://bitwarden.com/help/cli/
